<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="505" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,222,787]" pageId="18" pageNumber="505">
This species always has three strong orange spots on the fore wing upper side. Occasional specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Metisella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrisignatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="505">M. quadrisignatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have reduced spotting, but it is the spot in space 5 which is lost first, so the markings never coincide with those of 
<taxonomicName box="[302,459,511,534]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Metisella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trisignatus">
<emphasis box="[302,459,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="505">M. trisignatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectionCode box="[472,553,511,535]" pageId="18" pageNumber="505">MJWC</collectionCode>
has not found the range of these two species to overlap, but this is not based on extensive collecting.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,222,787]" pageId="18" pageNumber="505">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1426520779" country="Kenya" location="Kisii" pageId="18" pageNumber="505" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Kisii">
Restricted to suitable parts of western 
<collectingCountry box="[635,711,583,607]" name="Kenya" pageId="18" pageNumber="505">Kenya</collectingCountry>
, in MJWCâ€™s experience this is mostly a forest species, although its capture at the 
<collectingRegion box="[342,396,618,643]" country="Kenya" name="Kisii" pageId="18" pageNumber="505">Kisii</collectingRegion>
Hotel
</materialsCitation>
, 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1426520781" country="Kenya" location="Kisii" pageId="18" pageNumber="505" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Kisii">
<collectingRegion box="[479,533,618,643]" country="Kenya" name="Kisii" pageId="18" pageNumber="505">Kisii</collectingRegion>
(see also 
<taxonomicName box="[645,764,618,643]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Metisella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="willemi">
<emphasis box="[645,764,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="505">M. willemi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), suggests it is more adaptable than that. Adult behaviour is similar to that of other orange spotted species of the genus (
<figureCitation box="[831,946,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="18.[151,255,1357,1380]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,842,1333]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,842,1333]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 22. Adults of Metisella trisignatus, Kakamega Forest. 1, 5 Apr 1990; 2, 6 Apr 1990." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265112/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="505">Figure 22</figureCitation>
). It is an occasional feeder at damp mud in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,271,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Metisella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kakamega">
<collectingRegion box="[151,271,690,715]" country="Kenya" name="Kakamega" pageId="18" pageNumber="505">Kakamega</collectingRegion>
</taxonomicName>
Forest
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,222,787]" pageId="18" pageNumber="505">
<bibRefCitation author="Larsen" box="[199,356,727,751]" pageId="18" pageNumber="505" refString="Larsen, T. B. (1991) The Butterflies of Kenya and their Natural History. Oxford University Press, Oxford, UK, 490 pp." type="book" year="1991">Larsen (1991)</bibRefCitation>
states that the food plants are various grasses, but this is an assumption. A possible caterpillar is described in the introduction to this section above (
<figureCitation box="[723,836,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1648,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,770,1624]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,770,1624]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 21. Caterpillar of a Metisella sp. collected on unidentified grass, Kakamega Forest, 14 Nov 1989. 1, 9 mm, 15 Nov 1989; 2, after three moults, 13 mm, 1 Jan 1990; 3, after four moults, 15 mm, 16 Jan 1990; 4, after six moults, 22 Feb 1990; 5, after seven moults, 14 mm, 12 Mar 1990; moulted once more and died 1 Apr 1990." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265111/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="505">Figure 21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
